  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Intended use scope: pre-market submission support for a Class II centrifugal blood pump operated under adult CPB flow conditions (3–6 L/min, 60–3600 RPM), predicting normalized index of hemolysis as the primary QoI to inform worst-case operating point selection. Decision authority: Biofluid Simulation Group, Morrison Medical Devices.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case-identification",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-cfd-hemolysis-credible-mrl2",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/fda-gcbp-cfd-hemolysis-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-piv-experimental-2013",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/fda-gcbp-hemolysis-bench-2015",
    "https://uofa.net/morrison/data/morrison-mesh-convergence-study-2023"
  ],
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
